Chahkanduk (Persian: چهكندوك, also Romanized as Chāhkandūk)[1] is a village in Baqeran Rural District, in the Central District of Birjand County, South Khorasan Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 19, in 6 families.[2]
